article.headline: Denver 66, Grambling St. 42
article.story: DENVER -- Rob Lewis scored his first double-double of the season with 15 points and 11 rebounds in Denver's 66-42 win over Grambling State on Monday night. Nate Rohnert added 14 points, while Brian Stafford finished with 11 and Andrew Hooper came off the bench to score 10 points for the Pioneers (5-6). Denver, which has won four straight, went on a 16-2 run early in the first half and went into halftime with a 39-18 lead. The Pioneers held the Tigers to 30 percent shooting from the floor and forced 13 turnovers. Ibrahim Kpaka led Grambling State (2-8) with 17 points and eight rebounds. Jamal Breaux came off the bench to score seven points.
